04c02a5f-f038-43c3-84b8-cf1baca54620.2bbab6f2-e809-4b4a-b278-e9fc8d7c612f.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

04c02a5f-f038-43c3-84b8-cf1baca54620.description=
Synopsis

    This flow retrieves a list of cluster names based on their assignment to a data center.
    getClusterNamesByDataCenter performs the following steps\:
      1. Determine whether the flow is meant to be run as a test or as an actual provisioning flow.
      2. If the flow is a test, use hard-coded values to complete the retrieval.
      3. If the flow is for actual provisioning, retrieve the Unified Storage cluster names by data center using the HPOO flow getUnifiedStorageComponentsbyDataCenter.
      4. Check that there are cluster names available in the data center.
      5. If cluster names are available, pass the list of names back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    dataCenter - The datacenter in which to create the customer's vServer (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.


Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow;  in this case a list of cluster names available on a specific data center.  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.
    Unknown - The data center does not contain any cluster names.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
